II. The Three Layers of the Acts 15 Key Frame\
\
1. Cosmological Layer (The Order of God\'92s Creation)\
	\'95	Rooted in Genesis 1 and the Law of Moses (Acts 15:21).\
	\'95	Physical Root: Creation was ordered with distinctions and boundaries (clean/unclean, Israel/nations).\
	\'95	Key Phrase: \'93Known to God from eternity are all His works.\'94 (Acts 15:18)\
	\'95	Key Frame: Divine design and moral law are grounded in creation order.\
\
2. Pneumatic Layer (The Movement of the Spirit)\
	\'95	Rooted in the outpouring of the Spirit at Pentecost and the Gentile conversion of Cornelius (Acts 10).\
	\'95	Key Insight: The Holy Spirit moves outside the boundaries of the Mosaic Law, yet fulfills it.\
	\'95	Physical Manifestation: Signs, wonders, and the Gentiles receiving the Spirit.\
	\'95	Key Verse: \'93God gave them the Holy Spirit, just as He did to us.\'94 (Acts 15:8)\
\
3. Covenantal Layer (The Fulfillment of the Prophetic Word)\
	\'95	Rooted in the prophets, especially Amos 9:11-12, quoted by James (Acts 15:16-17).\
	\'95	Key Insight: The restored tent of David symbolizes the Messianic Kingdom, where the Gentiles are included under Christ\'92s reign.\
	\'95	Key Verse: \'93So that the rest of mankind may seek the Lord.\'94 (Acts 15:17)\
\
