V. Key Theological Anchors in Acts 15\
\
1. Divine Inclusion Without Abandoning Order:\
	\'95	The Gentiles receive the Spirit without circumcision, yet moral boundaries remain (Acts 15:29).\
	\'95	Balance of Freedom and Form: The Spirit moves beyond the Law while affirming its eternal principles.\
\
2. The Restoration of David\'92s Tent:\
	\'95	David\'92s Tent (Amos 9) symbolizes a worshiping community gathered under Messianic reign.\
	\'95	This prophetic image connects temple, worship, and kingdom into one reality fulfilled in Christ.\
\
3. Pneumatic Discernment and Apostolic Authority:\
	\'95	The Spirit\'92s movement requires apostolic confirmation.\
	\'95	The Council represents divinely guided human governance within the Church.\
\
